title: Grateful Dead Live at Madison Square Garden on 1994-10-18
lineage: Schoeps CMC 521's > DAT > EAC v0.9 beta 4 (secure) > Soundforge 5 > CD Wave > mkwACT > SHN
description: Help On The Way-> Slipknot!-> Franklin's Tower, The Same Thing, Althea, Cassidy*, Childhood's End, Don't Ease Me In Iko Iko, Samba In The Rain, He's Gone-> Smokestack Lightning-> Truckin'-> Drums-> Space-> The Days Between-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: my final MSG show this was a pretty solid show. a fat help>slip>franklins opes the show and the second set reversal of the normal truckin>smokestack>he's gone was a nice change. i'm happy with this aud having the SBD on cd already this aud sounds pretty nice.

took some cheap blotter
like 5 mins. befor we

got into college the next day I was a senior in H.S. in Philly during the Fall '94 tour.  We'd gone to all three Spectrum shows and scored tickets to this one at MSG.  Knowing my parents would not approve a school-night adventure to NYC for a Dead show, I merely left them a note on the table saying "Going to NY to see the Dead.  Will sleep at Steve's and go to school from his house tomorrow."  Well, I did make it to school and when I got home, I received my acceptance letter to Pitt!  A big thanks to Admissions Office folks at Pitt for their hard work in sending that letter out quickly because once my paretns knew that I was into college they let me off the hook for the whole MSG escapade!  As far as the show goes, pretty good for '94.  I was there with Steve, Kushy, and Dirty Cohen.  We were all medicated, and had a great time.  I remember the He's gone and Iko.  But in the end, who cares anyway?  It's Jerry, it's live and we were there!  Happy, Healthy and Safe New Year to all, and let us hope that love will not forsake the days that lie between.
blah Going through fall 94 to find some hidden gems. This aint one of them. Bobby hardly represented all night. Was he ill? Strange

Pretty good for '94 I was off the bus by this tour, but it has fresh  setlist w/ a few new tunes.
favs are Same Thing, Smokestack and Cassidy. Solid show, but only a decent audience recording.  Leave out Childhood's End....sorry Phil.
Days Between Days Between...check it out. Really strong, Bobby is all distorted and Vince has a China Doll-esque harpsichord tone going on. Quite nice. Standout of the show
